全球口罩告急，多国采取紧急措施，中国制造或为“解药”？。
Global mask crisis, multi-national emergency measures, China-made or "antidote"?
中国经营报                      。
China Business News.
中国经营报。
China Business News.
与中国企业同步成长，对话商业领袖，传播商业理想，服务商业人群，《中国经营报》掌控中国商界绝对话语权。
Growing in step with Chinese companies, dialogue with business leaders, spreading business ideals, serving the business community, The China Business Administration controls the absolute voice of the Chinese business community.
。
.
随着新冠肺炎疫情在全球范围内扩散，“口罩荒”现象明显增多，不少国家开始禁止口罩出口。
With the global spread of the new crown pneumonia, "mask shortage" phenomenon has increased significantly, many countries began to ban the export of masks.
全球多地口罩告急韩国买口罩实行单双号随着新冠肺炎疫情加剧，韩国市场上“口罩荒”日益严重。
Global Mask Crisis South Korea Buys Face Mask Single / Double Number As the outbreak of new cases of pneumonia intensifies, the market is facing a growing shortage of face masks.
韩国将实施口罩限购措施：按照出生年份的奇偶数实施限购，奇数年出生的只能在奇数日期购买口罩；偶数年出生的只能在偶数日期购买；同时每人每周限购2只。
South Korea will implement a face-mask restriction based on the odd number of years of life. Those born in odd years can only buy them on odd days; those born in even years can only buy them on even-numbered days; and two face-to-face restrictions per person per week.
此外，政府还决定将通过药店、农协超市和邮局等公共渠道销售的口罩比重，从目前的50%扩大到80%以上，并为口罩生产商提供各种支援，将口罩单日产量从目前的约1000万只增加到1400万只。
The government has also decided to increase the proportion of face masks sold through public channels such as pharmacies, farmers' associations, supermarkets and post offices from 50 per cent to more than 80 per cent, and to provide various support to mask manufacturers, increasing their daily production from about 10 million to 14 million.
另据韩国《中央日报》网站3月4日报道，截至3日，在韩国各地邮局启动口罩定点销售三天后，市民们仍在因口罩供应短缺和排队购买的方式而苦不堪言。
As of March 3, after three days of targeted sales of face masks at post offices across South Korea, citizens are still suffering from a shortage of masks and queuing up to buy them.
部分地区有人凌晨3点50分就来到邮局门口排队，等待7个多小时才能买到5个口罩。
Some people line up at the post office at 3: 50 a.m. and wait more than seven hours to buy five masks.
法国紧急征用口罩参考消息报道，由于新冠肺炎疫情迅速蔓延，法国政府征用所有口罩库存。
The French government has requisitioned all its masks in view of the rapid spread of pneumonia in the New Crown.
总统马克龙在推特上宣布：“我们征用所有防护口罩库存和生产线。
President Macron announced on Twitter: "We are commandeering all our masks stocks and production lines.
”他说，口罩将被发放给医护人员和感染新冠病毒的法国人。
He said the masks would be distributed to health-care workers and Frenchmen infected with the new cap virus.
政府也希望以此防止恐慌性抢购。
The government also wants to prevent panic buying.
法国卫生部长奥利维耶·韦朗说，法国迄今已从战略储备中释放1000万个口罩，通过全国各地的药店将它们提供给医院和医生。
French Health Minister Olivier Whelan says France has so far released 10 million masks from its strategic stockpiles and made them available to hospitals and doctors through pharmacies across the country.
法国的口罩总储备量约为1.6亿个。
France has a total stock of about 160 million masks.
目前很多药店的口罩已销售一空，一些卖家开始高价兜售。
Many pharmacies now have sold out of masks, and some sellers are selling them for high prices.
日本政府禁止转卖口罩据日本广播协会（NHK）电视台统计，截至当地时间6日10点半，日本国内确诊病例新增31例，累计确诊361例（含包机归国14例）。
Japan's government has banned the sale of face masks. As of 10: 30 am local time, 31 new cases have been confirmed in Japan, including 14 cases returned from chartered flights, according to the Japan Broadcasting Association (NHK) television.
日本厚生劳动省5日晚宣布，之前离船入住政府设施等接受隔离的部分“钻石公主”号邮轮乘员乘客中，又有8例确诊。
Japan's Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare announced Thursday that eight more cases were confirmed after disembarking from government facilities and other quarantined passengers on board the MV Princess Diamond.
此外，为减少之前的重复统计，厚生劳动省将“钻石公主”号邮轮确诊病例调整为696例。
In addition, to reduce the previous double counting, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare adjusted the number of confirmed cases of "Princess Diamond" to 696.
鉴于目前日本口罩短缺，日本政府将根据《国民生活安定紧急措施法》禁止转卖口罩，违者将被处以罚款。
In view of the current shortage of face masks in Japan, the Government will ban the resale of them under the Emergency Measures for the Stability of National Life Law, under penalty of a fine.
这是日本首次依法禁止转卖口罩。
It was the first legal ban on the sale of face masks.
此外，日本政府还将采购2000万只可再利用的纱布口罩，配发给护理机构和育儿机构等。
In addition, the Government will procure 20 million reusable gauze masks for distribution to care and childcare institutions, etc.
德国采取禁止口罩出口等多项措施据德国《欧洲时报》，德国当地时间3月5日23时30分公布的统计数据，截至3月5日23时30分，德国已累计确诊新冠肺炎患者565例，一天内确诊病例增加近200例，德国已成为中国境外国家中继韩国、意大利、伊朗、日本后感染人数第五高的国家。
Germany has confirmed 565 new cases of pneumonia and nearly 200 more cases in a single day, making it the fifth-highest country outside China to infect South Korea, Italy, Iran and Japan, the European Times said.
当地时间3月4日，德国政府出台了禁止包括口罩在内的医疗防护用品出口、呼吁在欧盟其它国家的德国人就地隔离、强化联邦和各州协作等多项措施，以加强疫情防控。
Germany has imposed a ban on the export of medical supplies, including face masks, called for on-site segregation of Germans in other European Union countries, and strengthened federal and state coordination to strengthen disease control.
全球“口罩荒”，中国能做什么？此前，世卫组织总干事谭德塞就曾表示，全球市场已经被严重扰乱。
What can China do about the global "face mask crisis"? Mr Tanner, WHO's director-general, has said global markets have been severely disrupted.
口罩等个人防护用品的需求量已是正常水平的100倍，价格则是正常水平的20倍，且由于广泛地、不恰当地使用个人防护用品，这种短缺情况进一步加重。
The demand for personal protective equipment, such as masks, was 100 times the normal level and prices were 20 times the normal level, and the shortage was further exacerbated by the widespread and inappropriate use of personal protective equipment.
化解全球的“口罩荒”离不开中国制造。
Global "mask shortage" cannot be solved without Chinese-made.
据中新网报道，中国是口罩生产大国，年产量占全球约50%。
China is a big producer of face masks, accounting for about 50% of global annual production, according to Xinhua.
疫情发生前，中国的最大口罩日产能为2000多万只。
Before the outbreak, China had a maximum capacity of more than 20 million masks a day.
随着此次疫情蔓延，口罩需求量爆炸式增长，短期供需矛盾加剧。
With the spread of the epidemic, demand for masks explosive growth, short-term supply and demand intensified.
为此，中国官方、企业各界齐心协力，优先保障口罩企业用工、资金、物流、关键原辅料供应等需求，全力推动口罩企业开足马力生产，口罩供给得到明显改善。
To this end, Chinese authorities and enterprises have made concerted efforts to give priority to meeting the needs of mask enterprises in terms of labor, capital, logistics, and supply of key raw materials.
中国国家发改委3月2日发布消息称，据调度，2月29日，包括普通口罩、医用口罩、医用N95口罩在内，全国口罩日产能达到1.1亿只，日产量达到1.16亿只，分别是2月1日的5.2倍、12倍，进一步缓解了口罩供需矛盾。
According to dispatch regulations, on Feb. 29, the national production capacity of masks, including ordinary masks, medical masks and N95 face masks, reached 110 million, bringing the daily output to 116 million, or 5.2 to 12 times that of February 1, further easing the gap between supply and demand.
据官方数据，中国每年口罩出口数量稳定在生产规模的70%以上。
According to official figures, China's annual exports of masks have stabilized at more than 70% of production.
值得注意的是，此前有外媒报道称，中国因新冠肺炎疫情禁止出口医用口罩及生产所需的原材料，令其他国家和地区面临口罩短缺。
It is worth noting that foreign media reported that China's ban on the export of medical masks and raw materials for production of the new crown pneumonia has left other countries and regions facing a shortage of masks.
对此，中国商务部外贸司司长李兴乾5日称，中国未对口罩设置任何贸易管制措施，并愿意在口罩等医疗防护物资方面给予相关国家力所能及的援助。
China has not imposed any trade controls on masks and is willing to provide medical protection such as masks to the countries concerned, Li Xingqian, director of China's Ministry of Commerce's foreign trade department, said Wednesday.
针对一些国家在口罩、防护服等产品上采取了一系列出口限制措施的问题，商务部近日回应称，近期，出于对疫情蔓延的担忧或是本国防控需要，个别国家限制对华出口口罩、防护服、消毒液等疫情防控物资，对我们造成了一定负面影响。
In response to a series of export restrictions on masks and protective clothing from some countries, the Ministry of Commerce responded recently that some countries have restricted the export of respirators, protective clothing and disinfectant to China due to concerns about the spread of the epidemic or the need for national control.
我们对有关国家的做法和反应表示理解。
We understand the practices and reactions of the countries concerned.
也希望相关国家尊重世卫组织专家意见，继续给予中方充分理解和坚定支持，客观理性看待疫情影响，不采取过度的贸易限制措施。
It is also hoped that relevant countries will respect the WHO expert opinions, continue to give China full understanding and firm support, treat the impact of the epidemic objectively and rationally, and refrain from taking excessive trade restrictive measures.
